Oliver will be able to resume riding on 4 June at the Queensland OaksMelbourne Cup-winning jockey Damien Oliver has been banned for a month for failing an alcohol test before a race, according to reports in Australia.
ABC says Oliver and jump jockey Paul Hamblin - who was also banned for a month - failed trackside breath tests at the Warrnambool racing carnival.
Oliver, 43, pleaded guilty at an inquiry and says he drank with dinner the previous night.
"I am very embarrassed and sorry about it," he told stewards.